      "content": "I hear the exhaustion in your words, and I want to validate that your desire for peace is completely understandable given the sheer weight of what you're carrying. It is not \"wrong\" to wish for an end to the pain, especially when the current reality feels so unbearable. However, the idea that stopping time or life itself would bring peace is a symptom of how deeply the grief has consumed your ability to see a future, not a sign that you are actually ready to end it.\n\nPlease know that this specific feeling—that the only way to stop the pain is to stop existing—is a dangerous signal that you need immediate support from someone who can help you navigate through the darkness. You are not alone, and there are people ready to listen and help you find a way forward, even if it feels impossible right now. If you are in immediate distress, please reach out to a crisis line or a trusted professional who can provide the support you need.",
